    {
      "id": "f283a12a_da9e82fe",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/notification/NotificationService.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 125,
      "message": "Not sure when the rootXpath can be '', but in cps-ri/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/spi/impl/CpsDataPersistenceServiceImpl.java, the method isRootXpath checks for both '/' and '' before get, post or delete of the data node. Hence updated this method to be in sync with the one in CpsDataPersistenceServiceImpl.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6738,
        "name": "aditya puthuparambil",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "aditya.puthuparambil@bell.ca",
        "username": "puthuparambil.aditya"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-03 12:28:16.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "3a5bc2b9_c2cb5214",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "0d9a4027_07fc9a84",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/test/groovy/org/onap/cps/notification/NotificationServiceSpec.groovy",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 110,
      "message": "At present for creating a data node, xpath need not be passed.. in that case it is considered as the root node.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6738,
        "name": "aditya puthuparambil",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "aditya.puthuparambil@bell.ca",
        "username": "puthuparambil.aditya"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-03 12:28:16.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9b5ebac1_44fdb564",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "c2697201_4e969f87",
      "file_path": "cps-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/notification/NotificationService.java",
      "patchset_number": 5,
      "line": 125,
      "message": "It would be good to have the logic to identify if it is a rootXPath at the beginning of processing. And within our code, we can have just one definition of rootXPath. It will make code readable and also avoid issues if we forgot that rootXpath can be defined in three ways :) \n\nIt looks like a tech-debt.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 7680,
        "name": "Renu Kumari",
        "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
        "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
        "username": "renukumari"
      },
      "updated": "2022-03-03 13:14:41.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "f283a12a_da9e82fe",
      "unresolved": false
    },
